Rick and Morty Viewer
=====================

This application uses Qt 6 which is licensed under the GNU Lesser General
Public License (LGPL) version 3.

LGPL Compliance
---------------

This AppImage contains Qt shared libraries that you can replace with your
own modified versions. To do so:

1. Extract the AppImage:
   ./RickAndMortyViewer-*.AppImage --appimage-extract

2. Replace the Qt libraries in squashfs-root/usr/lib/

3. Run the extracted version:
   ./squashfs-root/AppRun

Qt Source Code
--------------

The Qt source code used in this application can be obtained from:
https://code.qt.io/qt/qt5.git (tag: v6.6.2)

Alternatively, you can download it from:
https://download.qt.io/official_releases/qt/6.6/6.6.2/

Submodules used:
- qtbase
- qtdeclarative
- qtshadertools
- qtsvg
- qtwayland

Build Configuration
-------------------

Qt was configured with:
  -shared -fontconfig -system-freetype -opensource

Third-Party Licenses
--------------------

- Qt: LGPL v3 (https://www.qt.io/licensing/)
- libcurl: MIT/X derivate license (statically linked)
- glog: BSD 3-Clause (statically linked)
- nlohmann/json: MIT (header-only)
- Roboto font: Apache License 2.0
- Noto Color Emoji: SIL Open Font License 1.1

Rick and Morty API
------------------

This application uses the Rick and Morty API (https://rickandmortyapi.com/)
which is free and open to use.
